	   <tr><td colspan=2>---------------------------------------------- <br>What are Focus items.<br>---------------------------------------------- <br><br>Items that help improve the stats/level/dmg&nbsp;&nbsp;of summoned pet.<br><br>They improve its size, and usually ac/hp/haste(agility) of the pet.<br><br>The focus items help summon a higher level pet.  Since pet damage is set by its level, a focus item helps summon a higher level pet. <br><br>Yes it is a higher level pet because if a lower level considers them, they will con a bit differently.<br><br>Anyone who says it doesnt affect the level of the pet is wrong.<br><br>---------------------------------------------- <br>What level do they work.<br>---------------------------------------------- <br><br>These four focus items from Temple of Ro are for lvl 34-44 pet spell levels.  They wont change the stats of the pet before 34 or 49+ pet spells.<br><br>Only the elemental staffs of mastery will work on 49+ pets.<br><br>Anyone testing the focus items on under lvl 34 pets is getting bad data aka (no level changes) which is wrong.<br><br>However a focus item will make a larger pet no matter what the level of the spell is.<br><br>---------------------------------------------- <br>Where do you get focus items.<br>---------------------------------------------- <br><br>Half-elf mage Vira in Temple of Ro in Lavastorm.<br><br>----------------------------------------------- <br>What does each focus quest require? <br>-----------------------------------------------<br><br>BROOM OF TRILON -<br>A Star Ruby - jewel vendor<br>A Feather -  from a Griffon, griffawns also drop them in NK (lvl 18-21).<br>A Broom -  Magician in Cazic-thule or Najena. <br>Toes of a Cyclops - Rathe mts, OOT, maybe Oasis - ancient cyclops.. not sure.. <br><br>  <br>SHOVEL OF PONZ -<br>A Ruby - jewel vendor<br>Eye of a Gargoyle - OOT or Mist Moore.<br>A Shovel - from a Magician in Cazic-Thule or Najena. <br>Toes of a Hill Giant - Rathe Mts, WC, other zones...<br><br>  <br>TORCH OF ALNA -<br>A Fire Emerald - jewel vendor<br>A Scale -  from a Fire Drake (Lavastorm). <br>A Torch -  Magician in Cazic-Thule or Najena. <br>Toes of a Fire Giant - Sol B or gornit a lvl 35 HG in OOT.. <br><br>STEIN OF ULISSA -<br>A Sapphire - jewel vendor<br>A Scale - From a Mermaid -  OOT<br>A Stein - Magician in Cazic-Thule or Najena. <br>Toes of a Frost Giant - Everfrost or Gornit in OOT. <br><br>Gornit is a lvl 35 HG on Sea fury isle.. Sea furies are lvl 42 and drop cyclops toes.<br>Gornit drops all toes, random drop...<br><br>------------------------------------------------------------------  <br>Where can i find info or pictures of these items?<br>------------------------------------------------------------------ <br><br>Both can be found on this page<br><br><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Quests/Focus_Items.htm" target=_new>http://www.magecompendium.com/Quests/Focus_Items.htm</a><br><br><br>------------------------------------------------------------------  <br>Where can i get more mage info?<br>------------------------------------------------------------------ <br><br><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com" target=_new>http://eq.castersrealm.com</a> - great for casters<br><a href="http://eq.stratics.com" target=_new>http://eq.stratics.com</a> - not a bad site.<br><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com" target=_new>http://www.magecompendium.com</a> - Ultra site for mages I just found (kudos to you man)<br><a href="http://www.eqvault.com" target=_new>http://www.eqvault.com</a><br><br>and off course the old big daddy  <a href="http://www.everlore.com" target=_new>http://www.everlore.com</a><br>------------------------------------------------------------------ <br>&nbsp;<br>Eendyar Soulseeker<br>46'th High Elf Mage <br>"Mythic Synergy"<br><a href="http://www.mythicsynergy.com" target=_new>http://www.mythicsynergy.com</a><br>Fennin Ro</td></tr>
